<h2>Size-up</h2>
<div id="links"><IMG SRC="/edu/vehicle_fires/images/VF-Figure05.jpg" border="1" align="right" width="350" height="300">
<ul>
<li>Perform a <a href="#">sizeup <span>An on-going process of gathering and analyzing information critical to incident factors that lead to problem identification.</span></a> and give a verbal report on the radio. </li>
<li>The report should include:</li>
	<ul>
		<li>Name of unit that is on the scene</li>
		<li>Establishment of command using a command identifier - usually the name of the street (mile markers for interstates).</li>
		<li>The location of the incident if different from the original dispatch.</li>
		<li>Short description of what you see - the number and type of vehicle(s) involved, the degree of<br>fire involvement (if any), the description of exposures (if any), the status of traffic flow.</li>
		<li>Declare strategy, if applicable.</li>
		<li>Declare level two staging area, if applicable.</li>
		<li>Request additional resources, if necessary.</li>
	</ul>
<li>Continue to actively "size-up" the incident scene.</li>
</ul>
